/span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on – Governmental </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">O</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rganization whose main goals are to cultivate a strong reading culture </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">among children in Tanzania through the provision of books t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o children for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the purpose</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of increasing and widen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing their knowledge and develop</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing their reading skills; for the teaching of literacy and support for reading </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in the formal education system throug</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">h in – service training of teachers and supporting indigenous authorship and publishing.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Description of CBP Activities</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CBP programme has three main components which include:</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Teacher training through in service teacher training through the Training of Trai</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ners mode</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">l</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(TOT). Teachers receive 15 days of training and on – going, in class support to upgrade their knowledge skills and qualification in the teaching of reading and writ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Training of trainers</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CBP implements a professional development for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Trainers. This</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">led</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by CBP’s experienced staff. Trainers are trained for 15 days divided into three 5 – day workshop sessions spread out</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> over 8 months. </span></p><ol start="3" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 31.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Book Provision for Children</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In addition to training of teachers, CBP provides reading materials to help children learn to read and develop life – long habits of reading. Schools are supplied with reading materials and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">teachers are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> given training in library management and in reading p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">romotion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><ol start="4" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Book Sector Training</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CBP provides book sector training to publishers, writers, illustrators and editors, with the aim of development professional skills to them hence improving the quality of the books produced.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3.0 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Provision</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">of Braille Books for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Visually Impaired Children</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Rationale for the Project</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In 1994 CBP organized a Children’s Book Day at the National Library. Among the invited children where visually impaired children from Uhuru Mchanganyiko, in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Ilala District</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, Dar es Salaam region. The children </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">performed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> a poem which raised their voice that they were being neglected in CBP’s book project </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">activities, while normal ch</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ildren were provided with books</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The children raised their concern that, they had very few textbo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">oks in Braille and there were no reading books. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Following the request, CBP embarked on a programme of producing Braille books for visually impaired children. Those were the first readers ever produced for visually impaired children in the countr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">y</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> To-date</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CBP has transcribed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 37 story books for visually impaired </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">children. The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> books have been distributed to 25 schools which cater for the disabled children.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Currently there are more than 2,000 visually impaired children in primary schools in Tanzania. Among th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">em are two specials namely Bwigili in Dodoma region and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Furaha in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Tab</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ora region. There are also integrated schools which are Uhuru Mchanganyiko in Dar es Salaam,Mazinyungu in Morogoro region and another one in Lushoto, the rest are inclusive schools.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">4.0 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Challenges</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Children</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Visually impaired school children face severe shortage not only of textbooks but also of readers. Reading books have been found to help children retain the longest memories as compared to the content of textbooks the childre</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">se in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> primary schools.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Children are inhibited due to the denial of an opportunity to read books other than </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">textbooks</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, consequently</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Children</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> have lost the interest to read.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Children fail to develop wide knowledge, and cannot exhibit great potential for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">creative</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ness, life</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> skills such as self esteem, confidence, and inventiveness and their overall performance in their studies in all subjects.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Children miss the opportunity to read books to learn and learn to read. There are cases of children who complete </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">STD</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> VII wi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">thout knowing how to read and write.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Teachers</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Lack of basic librarianship skills results in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> low management of school libraries</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> even where Braille books are provided. This is evidenced by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> a CBP visit to one of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">integrated school</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in Kilosa, where such books were not well kept, they were torn and papers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">littered around</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the room which was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">meant</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to be a school library.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Teachers lack skills in the teaching of reading, a result of the low emphasis given to the teaching of reading in the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> colleges.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Teachers lack skills in producing their own materials for the teaching of reading and writing.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Teachers lack skills in promoting reading in their scho</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ols.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5.0 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Recommended</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Activities</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Needs Assessment</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CBP will carry out needs assessment to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">determine the actual number of visually impaired children who are in primary schools in Tanzania. The number of visually impaired children will d