-size:12pt">The Braille book provision i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nitiative strongly supports PED</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> III which states the necessity for school libraries and supplementary materials </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to support </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">learning and teaching.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Provision of Braille Books to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">integrated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> schools which cater for visually</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> impaired</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> children </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inclusive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> schools </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">support instruction strategies, literacy development and learning outcomes. These materials will support the quali</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ty of education, the country’s literacy development and nurture children’s lifelong habits of reading during a formative period of learning.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CBP has participated in the preparation of the government (Ministry of Education and Vocational Training) proposal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on Literacy and Numeracy (LANES) to the Global Partners Education (GPE) which has been approved. The proposal to GPE did not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> neither</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> accommodate an activity for provision of reading </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">books </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to both normal and visually impaired children nor establishment of s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">chool libraries</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Furthermore, the new presidential Initiative Big Results Now (BRN) and the PEDP III activities did not also accommodate the same. In this respect CBP is appealing to DFID to take the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">responsibility to provide Braille Books to improve the c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">hildren’s outcome and eventually contribute to improving the quality education.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>